snippet.textDisplay:
In November 2017 I had the chance to meet and talk with Stan Lee. When I did one of the things I asked was if he was interested in making a Black Widow movie. He said that her story was too large to be encompassed in one movie, but that he was definitely working on something for her. He also went on to tell me that there would be massive crossovers between characters in later films and that there would eventually be a solo project for every character who has ever existed in the Marvel universe. He said that he only wished he could live long enough to see it all, but that he probably wouldn't.

I wish he had been wrong.
snippet.textOriginal:

He also went on to tell me that there would be massive crossovers between characters in later films and that there would eventually be a solo project for every character who has ever existed in the Marvel universe. snippet.textDisplay:
anyone else bummed we don't get any consistent through-line to her story, just a bunch of unrelated relationships and bits? the Ultron Widow/Hulk pairing was such a narrative misstep. If they had kept her consistently involved with Clint it would have worked to build a meaningful relationship so [spoiler] in Endgame would have been more important. Then have this movie involve whatever happened in Budapest that originally started their relationship. So we go from the end back to the beginning. It could have had a Lance Hunter cameo for bonus points too.

but nah, meaningful long-term character development arcs are only for Cap, Tony, Bruce, Barton, Fury, Thor, Coulson... wait a second, meaningful long term character development is for guys? Are you seriously telling me Daisy is the only female MCU character who gets a multi-year character growth/development arc?

It could have had a Lance Hunter cameo for bonus points too.

but nah, meaningful long-term character development arcs are only for Cap, Tony, Bruce, Barton, Fury, Thor, Coulson... wait a second, meaningful long term character development is for guys?  Are you seriously telling me Daisy is the only female MCU character who gets a multi-year character growth/development arc?
